    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-01-07T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-01-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">718.1915/758: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-07T10:00:00-06:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1926—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2. Department’s telegram number 29 dated December 29, 1925, 7 p.m.</p>
                <p>Costa Rica has rejected Fabrega’s counterproposal for rectification of the
                    boundary and his proposal to postpone the negotiations until May.</p>
                <p>I shall forward on January 9 a memorandum on the final conference between
                    President Jiménez and Fabrega.<note n="46" xml:id="d322fn46">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
